<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="155" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[131,778,1709,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">
DIAGNOSIS. — Shell covering about 40-45% of dorsal surface area. Valves slightly longer than wide; colour white with some valves orange, showing a white portion with random orange spots. Valve i sculptured by raised ridges on the upper quarter portion and small tegmental pustules on the apex, which increase in dimension toward the margin. Valves ii-vii sculptured as valve i, except for jugal areas, which are sculptured by similar-sized tegmental pustules on the entire surface (
<figureCitation box="[507,587,1895,1919]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1962,1980]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-28@4.[698,1267,768,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — A‒E, Stenoplax marcusi (Righi, 1971); A, B, lateral view; C, frontal view; D, dorsal view; E, posterior view; F-J. Acanthochitona terezae Guerra-Junior, 1983; F, G, lateral view; H, frontal view; I, dorsal view; J, posterior view; K‒O, Acanthochitona ciroi Righi, 1971; K, L, lateral view; M, frontal view; N, dorsal view; O, posterior view; P‒T, Acanthochitona oxum n. sp.; P‒Q, lateral view; R, frontal view; S, dorsal view; T, posterior view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6335680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6335680/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Fig. 1N</figureCitation>
). Valve viii elliptic, antemucronal area straight and sculptured as valves ii-vii; mucro median, postmucronal area straight, sculptured as valve i (
<figureCitation box="[685,763,1948,1972]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1962,1980]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-28@4.[698,1267,768,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — A‒E, Stenoplax marcusi (Righi, 1971); A, B, lateral view; C, frontal view; D, dorsal view; E, posterior view; F-J. Acanthochitona terezae Guerra-Junior, 1983; F, G, lateral view; H, frontal view; I, dorsal view; J, posterior view; K‒O, Acanthochitona ciroi Righi, 1971; K, L, lateral view; M, frontal view; N, dorsal view; O, posterior view; P‒T, Acanthochitona oxum n. sp.; P‒Q, lateral view; R, frontal view; S, dorsal view; T, posterior view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6335680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6335680/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Fig. 1O</figureCitation>
). Perinotum white with transversal orange stripes, with 16 spicule tufts; margins with hyaline spicules.
</paragraph>
